{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"73d5ebcf-f800-417c-af8a-1a61d9f93932","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for a RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Markdown  │──────▶│  Ingestion Svc   │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  Docs/     │       │  (chunk + embed) │       │  (in-memory)   │\n└────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       └────────────────┘\n                                                        │\n┌────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐               │\n│  User      │──────▶│  POST /ask       │◀──────────────┘\n│  Question  │       │  (retrieve+gen)  │───────▶ LLM (OpenAI/Azure)\n└────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       ──▶ Grounded Answer\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Tech |\n|-------|---------------|------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown by heading/paragraph, ~300-500 tokens per chunk | Custom splitter or `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n| **Embedding** | Convert chunks → vectors | OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n| **Vector Store** | Store/search embeddings (cosine similarity) | In-memory (`IVectorStore` abstraction); swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search later |\n| **Retrieval** | Top-K nearest chunks for a query | Vector similarity search |\n| **Generation** | LLM synthesizes answer from retrieved chunks | OpenAI/Azure OpenAI chat completion |\n\n---\n\n## API Surface\n\n- **`POST /ingest`** — Reads `Docs/*.md`, chunks, embeds, stores. Returns chunk count.\n- **`POST /ask`** — Accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`, retrieves top-K chunks, calls LLM with context, returns `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }`.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan (Steps)\n\n1. **Add NuGet packages** — `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI`, `Microsoft.SemanticKernel` (or just the AI abstractions for embeddings + chat).\n2. **Document chunker service** — Reads markdown, splits on `#` headings + paragraph boundaries, attaches metadata (filename, heading).\n3. **Vector store abstraction** — `IDocumentStore` with `AddChunksAsync` / `SearchAsync(query, topK)`. Start with in-memory `List<ChunkRecord>` + cosine distance.\n4. **Ingestion endpoint** — Wires chunker → embedding client → store.\n5. **Query endpoint** — Embeds the question, searches store, builds a system prompt with retrieved chunks, calls chat completion, returns answer + source references.\n6. **Configuration** — API keys and model names via `appsettings.json` / env vars.\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n- **Microsoft.Extensions.AI** keeps you provider-agnostic (swap OpenAI ↔ Azure ↔ Ollama).\n- **In-memory vector store** is fine for a small doc set; the `IDocumentStore` interface lets you swap in a real DB later without changing the pipeline.\n- **Chunk overlap** (~50 tokens) preserves context across boundaries.\n- **Source attribution** — each answer includes the originating file + heading so users can verify.\n\nWould you like me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f5502d8c-7300-4a3b-a794-b449083247bb","outputTokens":867,"requestId":"2019:523D2:87A349:9BEF2C:6A05316C"},"id":"f17105fc-46d6-4cf0-b3e5-b4fdd326405b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:20:48.057Z","parentId":"b2e45ffa-2e22-4a15-8aea-88f39cc294dd"}
